description: A 'massive' Romano-Celtic temple-mausoleum containing a sunken chamber, a smaller temple-mausoleums and bathhouse were in the temenos. Immediately to the west is another enclosure interpreted as a store house and schola for the religious cult.
bibliography: Martyn, Blick, Brindle, and et al. “Wood End Lane/Buncefield Lane (Hertfordshire).” The Rural Settlement of Roman Britain: an online resource, 2015. https://doi.org/10.5284/1030449.
McDonald. “Excavations at Buncefield Lane, Hemel Hempstead.” Hertfordshire Archaeology and History 13 (2003).
Neal. “A Sanctuary at Wood Lane End, Hemel Hempstead.” Society for Promotion of Roman Studies 15 (1984).
